of a payment made, or the date an account was opened or closed. These claims directly correlate to the
Payment Rating and Account Status fields, demanding that the Metro 2 expert validate data input against the
source documents of the relationship.
A crucial component of efficient defense is knowing the exemptions. The regulation specifies exceptions where
the investigation requirements do not apply, such as disputes related to general identifying information (name,
address), inquiries, or information derived from most public records. Recognizing these exempt disputes allows
the legal and compliance teams to efficiently prioritize mandated investigations, preventing the unnecessary
allocation of resources to non-actionable complaints and streamlining internal legal expenses.
